         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden ¶ 23/3/63. ¶ Dear Dr Hooker. ¶  ¶ I have to send a brief reply to your last letter ¶ J. Hooker to M, 24 December 1862. ¶  ¶ Your acknowledging the validity of Macropteranthes in ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">63.03.23a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, un-numbered folio after f. 95.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">23/3/63.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Dr Hooker.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to send a brief reply to your last letter<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Hooker to M, 24 December 1862.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Your acknowledging the validity of Macropteranthes in Combretaceae is very pleasing to me. I send a new (i.e. third) species found during Stuarts last expedition. I named after Stuarts principal Officer, who seems to have gathered some of the plants of Stuarts expedition.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M named<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Macropteranthes kekwickii</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in B63.04.01, p. 151, to honour W. D. Kekwick, second in command of John McDouall Stuart's expedition of 1861-2. He had been promoted second in command during an earlier expedition. See Threadgill (1922).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— I feel much obliged for your generosity of continuing your contributions towards our herbarium. Thanks to your goodness<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and that [after]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>equally well-meaning friends we have now accumulated already a very valuable herbarium of extra-Australian plants, important for comparisons, especially when we are able to trust so implicitly on their correct naming, which we can in all that comes from Kew. — I trust that the woods are now all safely lodged at Kew and that the specimens were not curtailed.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Specimens exhibited at the International Exhibition, London, 1862.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall be happy to leave drawing up the description of the new grass to Colonel Munro, who will have a ready opportunity of introducing it into one of your periodicals.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Munro; in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>postscript to J. Hooker to M, 24 December 1862, Hooker reported Munro's proposed name, but said that he was writing to him to say that M would publish it. M published<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Panicum munroi</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">(B66.12.04, p. 204).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Very regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>dear Dr Hooker,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours ever</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Pray give my best thanks to your venerable father for having sent me the completing numbers of the 4. vol of his admirable Genera filicum.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Hooker (1842).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">All</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ours shall go for inspection to Kew by next opportunity. Since you always show so much solicitious interest in what concerns me, it will be probably pleasing to you to hear, that the Emperor of France has condescended of conferring on me the Knighthood of the Legion of Honor.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Ordre Impérial de la Légion d’Honneur to M, 6 January 1863 (in this edition as 63-01-06a);<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>E.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Drouyn de Lhuys to M, 6 January 1863; and M to H. Barkly, 23<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>March 1863<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 63-03-23c).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Combretaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Macropteranthes</seg>
            </p>
         </div>
